Description: Fresh Trade in at our retail store. From 2007-2009 era. Nice Squier SSH Telecaster. Nashville Style. Duncan Design Pickups. Fresh set up from our luthier. Tunes and plays great. Minor wear and tear from careful use. The neck pocket has finish cracks (pretty common on these guitars). Minor surface scratches and paint dings on the black finish. Neck is straight with very little fret wear. The Guardian case shown is included. It has some tolex loose on the edges. Structually sound and will protect this guitar well during shipping and home care. Keys are included. I have done a google on it and found a MF link that has some specs. The Squier Vintage Modified Tele SSH has a gloss finished maple neck, gloss-chrome knurled knobs, Duncan Designed Mini Humbucker, Tele Stack and Strat Stack pickups for hum canceling, reverse control plate, vintage six-saddle bridge, and five-way switching. 9.5" radius allows for easy string bending.
